2
00:00:35.161 --> 00:00:39.957
OH MY GHOST

3
00:01:33.969 --> 00:01:35.638
25-year-old male.

4
00:01:35.721 --> 00:01:38.516
found unconscious on the steps
of a club in Itaewon.

5
00:01:38.641 --> 00:01:41.227
His vitals are unstable.
body temperature's 25 degrees

6
00:01:41.310 --> 00:01:42.728
with signs of hypothermia.

7
00:01:42.812 --> 00:01:44.146
-Again?
-Yes.

8
00:01:44.647 --> 00:01:45.773
Hey. again?

9
00:01:45.856 --> 00:01:48.317
I know. So many similar cases in a month

10
00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:49.401
in this heat.

11
00:01:49.485 --> 00:01:52.404
Maybe it's some kind of virus like Ebola.

12
00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:54.615
Ebola. my foot.

13
00:01:56.408 --> 00:01:59.912
I suspect it involves drugs.

14
00:01:59.995 --> 00:02:01.413
Hey. what'd the cops say?

15
00:02:01.497 --> 00:02:04.834
The victims were with a woman
just before the accident.

16
00:02:04.917 --> 00:02:05.835
And?

17
00:02:05.918 --> 00:02:08.921
They have decent jobs and all.

18
00:02:09.004 --> 00:02:10.840
but there's no link with the women.

19
00:02:10.923 --> 00:02:13.467
-Then who did it?
-I don't know.

20
00:02:14.218 --> 00:02:15.469
-By the way.
-Yes.

21
00:02:15.553 --> 00:02:17.805
all these women have one thing
in common.

22
00:02:17.888 --> 00:02:18.806
What is it?

23
00:02:19.431 --> 00:02:20.599
-Every one of them
-Yes?

24
00:02:21.183 --> 00:02:22.393
is a beautiful woman

25
00:02:24.228 --> 00:02:25.396
with a killer body.

26
00:02:27.731 --> 00:02:29.149
-A killer body?
-A killer body?

27
00:02:29.859 --> 00:02:31.443
Who on earth is it?

28
00:02:31.527 --> 00:02:32.528
It can't be a ghost.

29
00:02:33.946 --> 00:02:34.947
Is it a ghost?

30
00:02:38.534 --> 00:02:40.536
That jerk turned me on for nothing.

31
00:02:43.247 --> 00:02:44.665
That didn't go as planned.

32
00:02:47.084 --> 00:02:48.085
Damn it!

33
00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:50.087
What?

34
00:03:23.037 --> 00:03:24.038
I'm sorry.

35
00:03:32.588 --> 00:03:35.174
You see me?

36
00:03:40.596 --> 00:03:42.222
EPISODE 1

37
00:03:42.723 --> 00:03:46.060
{\an8}<i>Hi. I'm DJ Jin of Midday Music.</i>

38
00:03:46.644 --> 00:03:49.939
{\an8}Today's high is expected to reach
30 degrees Celsius.

39
00:03:50.022 --> 00:03:51.357
{\an8}On this hot summer day.

40
00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:55.069
{\an8}I'm sure you all have your own tip
to stay cool.

41
00:03:55.653 --> 00:03:58.072
{\an8}Fans and air conditioning are a must.

42
00:03:58.155 --> 00:04:00.783
{\an8}Watching a horror movie could help. too.

43
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:02.993
{\an8}Ghosts are scary.

44
00:04:04.328 --> 00:04:06.956
{\an8}But you know what. guys?

45
00:04:07.039 --> 00:04:08.916
{\an8}I read it in a book.

46
00:04:09.041 --> 00:04:10.709
We think ghosts are dressed in white

47
00:04:10.793 --> 00:04:14.880
with long black hair. in a haunted house.

48
00:04:14.964 --> 00:04:20.469
But in fact. they're right next to us
in our everyday lives.

49
00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:23.305
Ghosts. chatting with us.

50
00:04:23.389 --> 00:04:24.723
Nice weather.

51
00:04:27.101 --> 00:04:30.020
It's so hot. I don't want to do anything.

52
00:04:30.104 --> 00:04:31.146
I know.

53
00:04:31.230 --> 00:04:34.316
-What for lunch?
-I want bibimbap. Or cheonggukjang?

54
00:04:34.400 --> 00:04:35.651
Cheonggukjang sounds good.

55
00:04:35.734 --> 00:04:39.321
On a hot and humid day like this.
we should go for cold noodles.

56
00:04:39.405 --> 00:04:41.365
-Okay. cold noodles it is.
-I'm down.

57
00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:44.368
Let's eat some rice. Koreans need rice.

58
00:04:45.369 --> 00:04:46.954
Rice.

59
00:04:47.037 --> 00:04:48.330
Rice.

60
00:04:49.331 --> 00:04:50.332
Let's go.

61
00:04:53.127 --> 00:04:55.212
Darn it. They won't let me tag along.

62
00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:59.091
I wanted to hang with some hot guys.
But no luck.

63
00:04:59.174 --> 00:05:00.926
What else you got besides looks?

64
00:05:14.606 --> 00:05:16.025
<i>I am a ghost.</i>

65
00:05:17.109 --> 00:05:20.279
<i>A virgin ghost. with the most
bitter grudges of all ghosts.</i>

66
00:05:21.530 --> 00:05:23.991
<i>It was so painful it was
to die as a virgin.</i>

67
00:05:24.074 --> 00:05:26.827
<i>that I became a soul
still wandering around this world.</i>

68
00:05:27.828 --> 00:05:31.582
<i>They call me the queen of mischief.
the prankster in the ghost world.</i>

69
00:05:31.665 --> 00:05:33.208
<i>But I want to be understood.</i>

70
00:05:33.792 --> 00:05:37.129
<i>I am a poor spirit. with many regrets.</i>

71
00:05:38.213 --> 00:05:41.300
<i>And I'm very bored.</i>

72
00:05:49.349 --> 00:05:50.350
What's up with you?

73
00:05:53.437 --> 00:05:54.521
You're so cute.

74
00:05:56.356 --> 00:05:57.941
Do you wanna play with me?

75
00:05:59.443 --> 00:06:00.944
You can see me?

76
00:06:05.908 --> 00:06:07.076
Pass!

77
00:06:07.159 --> 00:06:08.744
No. ball!

78
00:06:13.832 --> 00:06:14.666
DId you see that?

79
00:06:15.292 --> 00:06:16.960
-Did you see that?
-What was that?

80
00:06:26.345 --> 00:06:29.681
Wow. the sky is so high.

81
00:06:33.102 --> 00:06:34.103
It's so blue.

82
00:06:36.980 --> 00:06:37.981
How beautiful.

83
00:06:46.156 --> 00:06:47.366
Oh. this is depressing.

84
00:06:48.242 --> 00:06:51.078
This won't do. I need some funeral food
to get energy.

85
00:07:18.313 --> 00:07:19.731
Dong-chul.

86
00:07:19.815 --> 00:07:21.483
Stir sauce in one direction.

87
00:07:21.567 --> 00:07:22.818
You think it's dalgona?

88
00:07:24.194 --> 00:07:25.070
Come here.

89
00:07:25.154 --> 00:07:27.614
Like this.

90
00:07:27.698 --> 00:07:29.491
It's just that my arm is tired.

91
00:07:29.575 --> 00:07:32.369
So do some exercise.
Maintaining your health is a skill.

92
00:07:32.452 --> 00:07:33.287
I see.

93
00:07:33.370 --> 00:07:36.248
You could easily pass
as a manager of a company.

94
00:07:36.874 --> 00:07:38.709
Who'd think you're younger than me?

95
00:07:38.792 --> 00:07:41.879
My goodness. it's hard to
speak informally to that face.

96
00:07:42.921 --> 00:07:44.506
You're so dumb.

97
00:07:44.590 --> 00:07:45.757
That's not true...

98
00:07:45.841 --> 00:07:48.594
He's not dumb. He's sharp.

99
00:07:48.677 --> 00:07:50.179
But in my opinion.

100
00:07:50.262 --> 00:07:51.972
he does look old for his age.

101
00:07:52.055 --> 00:07:54.433
but you look too young for your age.
Soul Chef.

102
00:07:55.434 --> 00:07:57.352
People think you're in your twenties?

103
00:07:57.436 --> 00:07:59.646
Twenties? Some thought
I was a high schooler.

104
00:07:59.771 --> 00:08:01.523
I almost talked informally to you.

105
00:08:01.607 --> 00:08:02.441
I know. right?

106
00:08:02.983 --> 00:08:04.443
Dong-chul. I'm sorry.

107
00:08:04.526 --> 00:08:05.861
-Sorry.
-It's okay.

108
00:08:06.695 --> 00:08:07.696
Hey. Joon.

109
00:08:08.530 --> 00:08:10.157
It's too thick.

110
00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:12.075
You think it's for braised short ribs?

111
00:08:12.159 --> 00:08:13.535
It's for soup broth.

112
00:08:13.619 --> 00:08:15.204
It has to be well-rested.

113
00:08:15.746 --> 00:08:18.040
Don't they teach this at <i>Le Cordon Bleu</i>?

114
00:08:18.665 --> 00:08:20.042
No. they didn't.

115
00:08:20.125 --> 00:08:21.793
You think I don't know that?

116
00:08:21.877 --> 00:08:23.003
I'm being sarcastic.

117
00:08:23.086 --> 00:08:24.421
Metaphors or irony...

118
00:08:25.464 --> 00:08:27.382
You don't even budge even if I roast you.

119
00:08:27.466 --> 00:08:28.800
I should just fire you.

120
00:08:28.884 --> 00:08:30.802
Can't you smell something burning?

121
00:08:30.886 --> 00:08:32.554
It's burning inside me.

122
00:08:33.430 --> 00:08:35.474
I don't like those who studied abroad.

123
00:08:35.557 --> 00:08:38.477
Good qualifications are useless
when you have poor character.

124
00:08:38.560 --> 00:08:40.270
Something's definitely burning.

125
00:08:42.940 --> 00:08:43.857
It's from outside.

126
00:08:46.902 --> 00:08:47.736
Hey!

127
00:08:47.819 --> 00:08:50.030
-Hey.
-Na Bong-sun. are you insane?

128
00:08:50.113 --> 00:08:51.990
-I'm sorry.
-Gosh.

129
00:08:52.074 --> 00:08:53.951
Look at the smoke.
What do we do?

130
00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:56.703
How could you fall asleep
while cooking the sauce?

131
00:08:57.329 --> 00:08:59.248
I'm sorry. Sous Chef. I'm so sorry.

132
00:08:59.331 --> 00:09:00.666
Is saying sorry enough?

133
00:09:00.749 --> 00:09:02.042
We almost had a fire.

134
00:09:02.125 --> 00:09:04.169
You don't even have the basics down.

135
00:09:04.253 --> 00:09:05.671
I should just fire you.

136
00:09:05.754 --> 00:09:07.589
You nearly burned down this place.

137
00:09:08.257 --> 00:09:09.258
I'm sorry. Sous Chef.

138
00:09:09.675 --> 00:09:11.176
It's not your restaurant. though.

139
00:09:11.802 --> 00:09:12.803
Oh. my.

140
00:09:14.429 --> 00:09:17.266
I thought this was the Himalayas.

141
00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:19.393
With this thick fog.

142
00:09:20.227 --> 00:09:22.437
The view is stunning.

143
00:09:23.939 --> 00:09:24.856
Isn't it?

144
00:09:34.825 --> 00:09:36.743
Min-soo. what are you in this kitchen?

145
00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:39.621
-Sous Chef.
-Then you're number two.

146
00:09:40.998 --> 00:09:43.834
Seems like you love this restaurant
as your own.

147
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:44.876
And yet.

148
00:09:45.711 --> 00:09:47.629
you left the sauce to this novice?

149
00:09:49.214 --> 00:09:50.382
Well. you know.

150
00:09:50.465 --> 00:09:53.343
I was watching it and left it
to her for just 10 minutes.

151
00:09:53.427 --> 00:09:55.178
She fell asleep in that short moment.

152
00:09:55.262 --> 00:09:56.513
No moments are short.

153
00:09:57.222 --> 00:09:58.974
It determines life or death.

154
00:09:59.057 --> 00:10:00.309
Yes. I'm sorry.

155
00:10:01.727 --> 00:10:04.438
I'm sorry. Chef. It's my fault.

156
00:10:04.521 --> 00:10:06.064
I know you talk behind my back.

157
00:10:07.107 --> 00:10:09.860
Well. it's okay. It's fine.

158
00:10:09.943 --> 00:10:12.571
Working here sucks and is freaking tough.

159
00:10:12.654 --> 00:10:15.365
It's hardcore labor. so you need some fun.

160
00:10:15.449 --> 00:10:17.534
No. Chef. How could I...

161
00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:19.745
-Come on.
-But passing your work onto others.

162
00:10:21.913 --> 00:10:23.498
and being unprofessional.

163
00:10:25.334 --> 00:10:26.335
I can't tolerate that.

164
00:10:27.669 --> 00:10:29.212
It's about character and basics.

165
00:10:29.921 --> 00:10:31.131
It can't be taught.

166
00:10:32.507 --> 00:10:33.842
I'll be careful. Chef.

167
00:10:35.677 --> 00:10:36.678
Do well. Min-soo.

168
00:10:37.346 --> 00:10:38.513
-Yes. Chef.
-Do well.

169
00:10:38.597 --> 00:10:40.474
-Yes. Chef.
-I'll see.

170
00:10:40.557 --> 00:10:41.475
Yes. Chef.

171
00:11:00.619 --> 00:11:03.705
I'm over thirty
yet I get scolded like a child.

172
00:11:04.748 --> 00:11:07.918
Damn it. this is so humiliating.
I should just open up my restaurant.

173
00:11:08.919 --> 00:11:10.253
I'm sorry. Sous Chef.

174
00:11:12.255 --> 00:11:13.465
Hey. Bong-sun.

175
00:11:14.841 --> 00:11:17.010
Hey. Bong. You damn bong.

176
00:11:18.387 --> 00:11:19.888
I mean...

177
00:11:19.971 --> 00:11:22.974
Why do you doze off in broad daylight?

178
00:11:23.058 --> 00:11:24.559
Why?

179
00:11:29.523 --> 00:11:31.775
-Do better. Okay?
-Yes.

180
00:11:34.277 --> 00:11:35.195
Darn it...

181
00:12:08.687 --> 00:12:11.231
Oh. no.

182
00:12:12.232 --> 00:12:13.608
Oh. no.

183
00:12:15.318 --> 00:12:16.987
It stings!

184
00:12:23.785 --> 00:12:27.789
Our Father who art in heaven.
hallowed be Thy name.

185
00:12:27.873 --> 00:12:30.792
The kingdom come. Thy will be done.

186
00:12:30.876 --> 00:12:32.419
on earth as it is in heaven.

187
00:12:44.890 --> 00:12:46.558
Yes. Grandma.

188
00:12:46.641 --> 00:12:49.186
<i>Why do you sound so down?</i>

189
00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:51.021
<i>Have you eaten?</i>

190
00:12:51.104 --> 00:12:53.648
Yes. what about you? Have you been well?

191
00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:55.525
<i>Me? Same old.</i>

192
00:12:56.067 --> 00:12:57.152
<i>How are you doing?</i>

193
00:12:57.986 --> 00:12:59.362
<i>Are you able to sleep at all?</i>

194
00:12:59.446 --> 00:13:02.073
<i>Are ghosts still bothering you?</i>

195
00:13:02.199 --> 00:13:03.992
No. I've been sleeping fine.

196
00:13:04.075 --> 00:13:05.994
They don't show up often these days.

197
00:13:06.578 --> 00:13:08.413
<i>That's good to hear.</i>

198
00:13:08.497 --> 00:13:12.000
<i>You shouldn't be a shaman like me.</i>

199
00:13:12.083 --> 00:13:16.505
<i>Make sure to light incense by your bed
and keep the knife there. okay?</i>

200
00:13:18.173 --> 00:13:19.007
Okay.

201
00:13:20.133 --> 00:13:21.301
I'm hanging up. Grandma.

202
00:13:28.767 --> 00:13:29.935
Oh. it stings.

203
00:13:30.977 --> 00:13:32.646
What do I do?

204
00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:38.318
Here. report card.

205
00:13:39.194 --> 00:13:40.529
Great job.

206
00:13:40.612 --> 00:13:42.030
I always do a great job.

207
00:13:42.906 --> 00:13:46.868
I'm a good cook. handsome. and witty.

208
00:13:46.952 --> 00:13:49.663
God is so unfair.
he's given me everything.

209
00:13:50.413 --> 00:13:53.333
You'd be perfect
if you weren't so full of yourself.

210
00:13:53.416 --> 00:13:56.211
That's a flaw I made on purpose.

211
00:13:56.294 --> 00:13:58.547
Because if I were too perfect.
I'd get hated.

212
00:14:01.132 --> 00:14:02.842
You're so nice and funny.

213
00:14:02.926 --> 00:14:04.928
But why are you so mean to only two women?

214
00:14:05.011 --> 00:14:05.887
Who?

215
00:14:05.971 --> 00:14:07.013
Bong-sun.

216
00:14:08.098 --> 00:14:10.767
You're so hard on her.
I think it makes her more timid.

217
00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:13.311
Well. she's annoying.

218
00:14:13.895 --> 00:14:15.063
Who's the other one?

219
00:14:16.064 --> 00:14:17.107
It's me!

220
00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.525
Perfect timing.

221
00:14:19.234 --> 00:14:20.902
-You're here. Mom?
-Yes.

222
00:14:30.245 --> 00:14:31.663
Are you here for inspection?

223
00:14:33.164 --> 00:14:35.083
You're distracting me. Could you sit?

224
00:14:35.625 --> 00:14:37.544
I asked you not come to the restaurant.

225
00:14:41.506 --> 00:14:42.966
Do I embarrass you?

226
00:14:43.049 --> 00:14:44.926
Why not? It's my son's restaurant.

227
00:14:45.010 --> 00:14:46.553
Because the customers ask

228
00:14:47.053 --> 00:14:48.305
if you're my aunt.

229
00:14:49.222 --> 00:14:51.182
Or if you're my secret lover.
who's older.

230
00:14:51.266 --> 00:14:52.267
That kind of nonsense.

231
00:14:52.976 --> 00:14:53.810
You were 19...

232
00:14:53.893 --> 00:14:55.395
I had you when I was 19. so what?

233
00:14:56.104 --> 00:14:58.398
It's my life. not theirs. Who cares?

234
00:14:58.481 --> 00:15:01.651
So live your life.
Why do you keep coming to my restaurant?

235
00:15:03.361 --> 00:15:04.613
Unbelievable.

236
00:15:04.696 --> 00:15:07.365
It's like he takes
some mean speech classes.

237
00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:11.828
Sun-woo.

238
00:15:14.581 --> 00:15:15.498
Sun-woo?

239
00:15:18.084 --> 00:15:19.044
Sun-woo.

240
00:15:20.170 --> 00:15:21.254
What is it?

241
00:15:21.338 --> 00:15:23.173
It's no big deal.

242
00:15:23.256 --> 00:15:26.051
You have fortune with only <i>yang</i> energy.

243
00:15:26.134 --> 00:15:29.387
You have immense <i>yang</i> energy.
this year you have a fortune with ghosts.

244
00:15:29.471 --> 00:15:31.598
Ghosts can follow you.

245
00:15:31.681 --> 00:15:34.267
-Isn't that awful?
-Who said so? Master Tae?

246
00:15:34.809 --> 00:15:37.479
No. this is from
Mr. Jang in Seongbuk-dong.

247
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:39.564
Mom.

248
00:15:39.648 --> 00:15:42.067
Mom. I'm really okay.
I don't believe in ghosts.

249
00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:44.819
Who told you to believe them?
Just keep it.

250
00:15:44.903 --> 00:15:46.863
Oh. I hate this.

251
00:15:46.946 --> 00:15:48.531
-But...
-I don't want to.

252
00:15:48.615 --> 00:15:51.826
You're a professor.
why are you so superstitious?

253
00:15:51.910 --> 00:15:53.912
Mom. do your students know
you're like this?

254
00:15:54.954 --> 00:15:56.998
-Seriously...
-Phone.

255
00:15:58.249 --> 00:15:59.250
Hey. So-hyung.

256
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:02.962
Yeah. I'm always so busy. Why?

257
00:16:03.046 --> 00:16:05.048
-Here.
-Hey.

258
00:16:05.715 --> 00:16:06.966
You're early.

259
00:16:08.093 --> 00:16:09.386
-Hey. guys.
-Welcome.

260
00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:13.014
-It's been a while.
-Indeed.

261
00:16:13.098 --> 00:16:15.308
I knew you'd come to
others' funeral banquet.

262
00:16:16.184 --> 00:16:18.353
No wonder you're hungry.

263
00:16:18.436 --> 00:16:21.773
You get no food offering.
so you must be starving.

264
00:16:22.941 --> 00:16:24.943
It's actually funny.

265
00:16:25.026 --> 00:16:27.946
Have you ever heard about
a ghost with amnesia?

266
00:16:28.029 --> 00:16:30.115
Right. It's not common.

267
00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:33.993
Fine. let's say it's because of
your trauma from your sudden death.

268
00:16:34.077 --> 00:16:39.457
But if you can't share your food offering.
you shouldn't want others'.

269
00:16:39.541 --> 00:16:41.501
Even ghosts should have some shame.

270
00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:45.088
They say appetite and sexual desire
go hand in hand.

271
00:16:45.171 --> 00:16:48.258
It's so obvious you're a virgin ghost.

272
00:16:49.008 --> 00:16:51.720
Hey. stop it. You don't even bother a dog
while eating.

273
00:16:51.803 --> 00:16:53.680
You think you're better than dogs?

274
00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:57.308
I heard you still possess women's bodies
to seduce men.

275
00:16:57.392 --> 00:17:00.270
I heard Seobinggo is
dead set on catching you.

276
00:17:00.353 --> 00:17:02.272
What does it have to do with you?

277
00:17:02.355 --> 00:17:04.399
It does have something to do with me!

278
00:17:04.899 --> 00:17:07.444
We're being treated the same
because of you.

279
00:17:07.527 --> 00:17:09.279
Why do something higher-ups forbid?

280
00:17:09.571 --> 00:17:10.864
Possession isn't allowed.

281
00:17:10.947 --> 00:17:13.199
As if you've never done anything wrong.

282
00:17:13.283 --> 00:17:15.785
I know you've done a lot of possessions
in the past.

283
00:17:15.869 --> 00:17:17.120
Let's see who's more crazy!

284
00:17:17.203 --> 00:17:18.997
-You want to fight?
-Let's fight.

285
00:17:19.080 --> 00:17:20.582
-Let's fight!
-Bring it on!

286
00:17:22.459 --> 00:17:24.335
What the heck? Where are you going?

287
00:17:24.419 --> 00:17:25.920
Are you scared to fight with me?

288
00:17:26.004 --> 00:17:28.673
Hey. let's have it out.

289
00:17:33.970 --> 00:17:35.597
You... you wench.

290
00:17:38.308 --> 00:17:39.267
How are you doing?

291
00:17:39.350 --> 00:17:41.561
I'm not doing well.

292
00:17:41.644 --> 00:17:44.105
How can I be well because of you?

293
00:17:44.189 --> 00:17:45.231
Well... I don't...

294
00:17:47.317 --> 00:17:49.402
-Eat your meal.
-Where are you going?

295
00:17:50.028 --> 00:17:51.196
You. you. stop!

296
00:17:52.155 --> 00:17:53.239
Hey. you wench!

297
00:17:56.618 --> 00:17:57.577
Come on.

298
00:18:02.248 --> 00:18:03.291
Hey!

299
00:18:04.959 --> 00:18:07.003
No. I'm not crazy.

300
00:18:07.086 --> 00:18:08.963
No. I have to catch her now.

301
00:18:09.047 --> 00:18:10.048
I'm not crazy.

302
00:18:15.970 --> 00:18:16.888
She's freaking fast.

303
00:18:17.639 --> 00:18:19.432
Stop there!

304
00:18:22.519 --> 00:18:25.104
You wench. how much yang energy
did you eat?

305
00:18:25.897 --> 00:18:26.773
I can't catch her.

306
00:18:26.856 --> 00:18:28.691
You wench. stop right there!

307
00:18:30.318 --> 00:18:31.986
That. that... bus!

308
00:18:32.529 --> 00:18:33.905
Taxi!

309
00:18:38.368 --> 00:18:40.078
Whoa. she's seriously...

310
00:18:51.172 --> 00:18:52.173
Is she crazy?

311
00:18:53.299 --> 00:18:54.175
Hey. you wench!

312
00:18:59.472 --> 00:19:00.306
Stop right there!

313
00:19:08.106 --> 00:19:09.190
Okay. let's hide here.

314
00:19:14.195 --> 00:19:15.655
Where did she go?

315
00:19:15.738 --> 00:19:17.115
Not again!

316
00:19:17.198 --> 00:19:18.616
Who else has she possessed?

317
00:19:20.368 --> 00:19:22.871
She's really testing my patience.

318
00:19:23.621 --> 00:19:25.164
You better come out. Huh?

319
00:19:25.248 --> 00:19:26.791
You better come out.

320
00:19:28.084 --> 00:19:29.919
Where the hell is she?

321
00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:35.300
-Sun-woo!
-Hey.

322
00:19:45.643 --> 00:19:47.103
You wench.

323
00:19:47.186 --> 00:19:48.021
You wench.

324
00:19:48.104 --> 00:19:49.355
I got you. you wench!

325
00:19:51.107 --> 00:19:52.859
Come here.

326
00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:54.527
-Get up already.
-Okay.

327
00:19:54.611 --> 00:19:55.528
Get up!

328
00:19:55.612 --> 00:19:56.446
Get up.

329
00:19:57.363 --> 00:19:58.781
You think I can't catch you?

330
00:19:58.865 --> 00:20:00.116
-Come.
-What's going on?

331
00:20:00.199 --> 00:20:01.117
Oh. come here.

332
00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:03.286
It hurts! Stop!

333
00:20:03.369 --> 00:20:05.079
Does it hurt? It hurts me too.

334
00:20:05.163 --> 00:20:06.998
You're so stressing me out.

335
00:20:07.832 --> 00:20:09.834
You're making a scene.

336
00:20:14.172 --> 00:20:15.298
Oh. seriously.

337
00:20:16.633 --> 00:20:18.009
She's unbelievable.

338
00:20:18.092 --> 00:20:19.469
When did she put this here?

339
00:20:20.261 --> 00:20:21.262
Oh. crap.

340
00:20:22.847 --> 00:20:25.725
Here's your lukewarm Americano.

341
00:20:26.309 --> 00:20:29.604
Right? You hate it hot.
because it messes with your taste buds.

342
00:20:29.687 --> 00:20:32.106
That's when I started working
in the kitchen.

343
00:20:32.190 --> 00:20:33.274
That's so long ago.

344
00:20:34.400 --> 00:20:35.693
What is it?

345
00:20:35.777 --> 00:20:37.070
Just say it. I'm busy.

346
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:39.822
Gosh. I know you're a busy man.

347
00:20:40.657 --> 00:20:43.576
In fact. I'm going into a new program.

348
00:20:43.660 --> 00:20:46.287
It's a survival cooking program
with viewers' requests.

349
00:20:46.371 --> 00:20:48.748
I'm thinking you and Chef Marco
in the first episode.

350
00:20:48.831 --> 00:20:50.208
Is he going to do it again?

351
00:20:50.667 --> 00:20:53.378
Gosh. he thinks he's a celebrity now.

352
00:20:53.461 --> 00:20:55.838
He has a star quality.
with unique background.

353
00:20:55.922 --> 00:20:57.507
What do you say? You'll do it?

354
00:20:58.132 --> 00:21:01.052
No. I don't do pilots. my friend.

355
00:21:02.303 --> 00:21:05.056
If it becomes a regular.
I'll think about it.

356
00:21:05.139 --> 00:21:06.140
Hey.

357
00:21:06.808 --> 00:21:09.477
-Even if I beg you?
-I better avoid going on air.

358
00:21:10.019 --> 00:21:13.439
I got distracted for a moment.
and the culinary world is a mess.

359
00:21:14.065 --> 00:21:15.483
You're so full of yourself.

360
00:21:15.566 --> 00:21:18.528
No. I'm just that good.
How many times have I told you?

361
00:21:18.611 --> 00:21:20.196
You're rejecting my offer?

362
00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:22.699
I really did earlier.

363
00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:27.078
I feel bitter.
I got rejected by a friend I trusted.

364
00:21:27.662 --> 00:21:30.081
-I guess this is life. huh?
-I'll get going.

365
00:21:31.040 --> 00:21:32.041
Hey.

366
00:21:32.125 --> 00:21:34.711
I'll go there this weekend.
You want to go with me?

367
00:21:36.504 --> 00:21:37.797
Maybe.

368
00:21:37.880 --> 00:21:39.590
He would want to be with you alone.

369
00:21:40.925 --> 00:21:41.843
Bye.

370
00:21:53.479 --> 00:21:54.647
Come here.

371
00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:59.819
Look away. I'm pressing the code.

372
00:22:00.903 --> 00:22:03.698
I'd try to get out.
You think I'd try to go in?

373
00:22:03.781 --> 00:22:05.116
Huh?

374
00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:06.784
You detailed wench.

375
00:22:08.703 --> 00:22:10.496
I better put the key inside.

376
00:22:12.749 --> 00:22:14.042
7182.

377
00:22:14.125 --> 00:22:15.293
I'll change it.

378
00:22:16.753 --> 00:22:18.838
SEOBINGGO FORTUNETELLER

379
00:22:25.928 --> 00:22:27.513
Help...

380
00:22:28.306 --> 00:22:29.307
Don't put on a show.

381
00:22:29.390 --> 00:22:32.143
These talismans don't hurt you.
They're just locks.

382
00:22:35.104 --> 00:22:37.565
Why only me?

383
00:22:38.316 --> 00:22:39.650
You want me to tell you?

384
00:22:39.734 --> 00:22:43.071
Because you went around doing possessions
and seducing men.

385
00:22:43.154 --> 00:22:45.615
the higher-ups are infuriated.

386
00:22:45.698 --> 00:22:49.035
Until I have you locked up.
they won't even let me read fortunes.

387
00:22:49.702 --> 00:22:51.204
Whatever. I love men so much.

388
00:22:51.996 --> 00:22:54.082
Of course you do. You're a virgin ghost.

389
00:22:54.165 --> 00:22:56.084
But you use other girls' bodies

390
00:22:56.167 --> 00:22:59.504
to seduce men you never flirt with
when you were alive?

391
00:23:00.379 --> 00:23:02.632
There's no point in trying so hard.

392
00:23:02.715 --> 00:23:05.093
What kind of man would have
enough <i>yang</i> energy

393
00:23:05.176 --> 00:23:06.719
to stand a ghost's <i>yin</i> energy?

394
00:23:06.803 --> 00:23:08.096
They say there is.

395
00:23:08.179 --> 00:23:10.389
A man with only <i>yang</i> energy.
with sunshine.

396
00:23:11.474 --> 00:23:14.143
That kind of man is one in a million.

397
00:23:14.227 --> 00:23:15.937
Where would you find him?

398
00:23:16.020 --> 00:23:17.939
I'm going to try.

399
00:23:18.022 --> 00:23:20.691
You said I'll turn into a scary demon.
after three years.

400
00:23:20.775 --> 00:23:23.027
I should relieve my regrets before that.

401
00:23:23.111 --> 00:23:25.321
That's why

402
00:23:25.404 --> 00:23:27.824
you need to discipline yourself.

403
00:23:28.491 --> 00:23:29.700
Let go of your grudges

404
00:23:29.784 --> 00:23:31.828
and let your soul belong in heaven.

405
00:23:31.911 --> 00:23:34.038
It's not as simple as it sounds.

406
00:23:34.122 --> 00:23:36.165
If you keep doing that

407
00:23:36.249 --> 00:23:40.378
and happen to meet a body
with the perfect frequency for you.

408
00:23:40.461 --> 00:23:44.215
you could get locked in
and never come out.

409
00:23:44.298 --> 00:23:45.299
Gosh.

410
00:23:50.304 --> 00:23:51.222
Jeez.

411
00:23:52.515 --> 00:23:55.017
Well. it's nice that you worry about me
and

412
00:23:57.311 --> 00:23:59.063
that I don't have to talk to myself.

413
00:24:03.109 --> 00:24:03.985
You...

414
00:24:06.737 --> 00:24:08.739
-You poor thing!
-What's gotten into you?

415
00:24:08.823 --> 00:24:11.200
I know how you feel.

416
00:24:11.284 --> 00:24:12.994
-My goodness.
-What's with you?

417
00:24:13.077 --> 00:24:15.746
Your voice is beautiful.
You're pretty.

418
00:24:15.830 --> 00:24:17.707
Come on. All right.

419
00:24:17.790 --> 00:24:20.209
Why are you so emotional today?

420
00:24:20.293 --> 00:24:22.378
-I love you.
-I love you. too.

421
00:24:23.713 --> 00:24:24.714
Perfect.

422
00:24:27.466 --> 00:24:28.384
What's this?

423
00:24:29.051 --> 00:24:30.219
What is it?

424
00:24:30.845 --> 00:24:32.555
How can I trust you?

425
00:24:32.638 --> 00:24:34.724
I should at least put a bell on you.

426
00:24:34.807 --> 00:24:37.727
Whoa! Am I a cat or dog or what?

427
00:24:39.937 --> 00:24:41.898
Hey. don't even try.

428
00:24:42.023 --> 00:24:44.859
Only I can untie it and hear it.

429
00:24:47.445 --> 00:24:48.529
Untie it!

430
00:24:48.613 --> 00:24:49.947
Untie it!

431
00:24:50.531 --> 00:24:52.283
Look at this. Oh my. maintenance fee.

432
00:24:52.366 --> 00:24:53.576
Oh. my God. 78.000 won.

433
00:24:53.659 --> 00:24:54.827
Why is it so high?

434
00:24:59.916 --> 00:25:01.167
Out of the way.

435
00:25:04.003 --> 00:25:05.588
There.

436
00:25:06.714 --> 00:25:07.715
Here.

437
00:25:11.093 --> 00:25:14.138
But don't you think we should have dinner?

438
00:25:14.222 --> 00:25:15.389
Chef is late today.

439
00:25:16.015 --> 00:25:17.600
What should we eat?

440
00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:23.022
Chef isn't here.
why don't we try some rice?

441
00:25:23.105 --> 00:25:24.023
Let's order in rice.

442
00:25:24.106 --> 00:25:25.066
Rice...

443
00:25:25.149 --> 00:25:27.235
Chef won't be happy when he comes back.

444
00:25:27.318 --> 00:25:29.779
Right. Chef hates rice.

445
00:25:29.862 --> 00:25:31.405
I don't want to get yelled at.

446
00:25:32.073 --> 00:25:34.367
That freaking Chef.

447
00:25:35.201 --> 00:25:37.703
So he's the chef and he hates rice.

448
00:25:37.787 --> 00:25:40.373
So what.
we have to eat noodles all the time?

449
00:25:40.915 --> 00:25:42.750
Oh. is he Nero or what?

450
00:25:42.833 --> 00:25:44.043
He's such a dictator.

451
00:25:44.126 --> 00:25:45.628
He never forced us.

452
00:25:45.711 --> 00:25:47.463
We're just walking on eggshells.

453
00:25:48.714 --> 00:25:50.091
<i>Cordon</i>. that bastard...

454
00:25:50.174 --> 00:25:52.551
Let's order in quickly.
before he comes back.

455
00:25:52.635 --> 00:25:55.846
I'm craving chive bibimbap
I used to eat.

456
00:25:55.930 --> 00:25:57.139
I want chive bibimbap.

457
00:25:57.223 --> 00:25:59.517
-Me too.
-Ox blood soup for me.

458
00:26:00.059 --> 00:26:01.394
Then...

459
00:26:01.477 --> 00:26:02.895
-Hey. Bong.
-Yes?

460
00:26:02.979 --> 00:26:04.855
Three chive bibimbaps. one ox blood soup.

461
00:26:04.939 --> 00:26:07.066
And you eat kimchi stew. To add soup.

462
00:26:07.149 --> 00:26:09.944
Are we really ordering?

463
00:26:10.653 --> 00:26:12.571
We are really ordering.

464
00:26:12.655 --> 00:26:15.116
Sous Chef says so. Who can say no?

465
00:26:15.199 --> 00:26:19.328
Come on. let's just sit at the table
and eat like noblemen today.

466
00:26:19.412 --> 00:26:22.039
Not like beggars.
eating in the kitchen all the time.

467
00:26:23.499 --> 00:26:26.627
You didn't eat yet?
Let's make spicy seafood noodle soup.

468
00:26:26.711 --> 00:26:28.379
-Yes. sir.
-Yes. Chef.

469
00:26:32.133 --> 00:26:33.217
Yes. Chef.

470
00:26:36.095 --> 00:26:38.014
Did the salmon get delivered?

471
00:26:38.848 --> 00:26:40.850
-Should I bring it?
-Yes. let's cut it.

472
00:27:04.165 --> 00:27:05.458
-Tweezers.
-Yes.

473
00:27:14.508 --> 00:27:15.426
Darn it.

474
00:27:17.386 --> 00:27:19.305
They sent us this crappy salmon.

475
00:27:20.973 --> 00:27:24.018
Are customers stray cats?
We can't feed them any fish.

476
00:27:24.101 --> 00:27:25.853
They're insane.

477
00:27:25.936 --> 00:27:27.063
Sous Chef. return this.

478
00:27:27.146 --> 00:27:29.523
Tell them if they keep cheating.
the deal is over.

479
00:27:29.607 --> 00:27:32.818
Yeah. Chef. I'm great at blackmailing.

480
00:27:32.902 --> 00:27:34.820
Chef. what about scallops from yesterday?

481
00:27:34.904 --> 00:27:35.863
They won't last long.

482
00:27:35.946 --> 00:27:38.449
Right. scallops. I ordered too much.

483
00:27:39.200 --> 00:27:40.034
What do we do?

484
00:27:40.701 --> 00:27:41.702
Is there spinach left?

485
00:27:42.411 --> 00:27:43.871
-Yes.
-Okay. Joon.

486
00:27:43.954 --> 00:27:46.207
Today's special is
scallop and spinach pasta.

487
00:27:46.290 --> 00:27:47.792
-Yes. sir.
-Got it?

488
00:27:47.875 --> 00:27:49.877
I guarantee it's good.
So recommend.

489
00:27:49.960 --> 00:27:51.045
Tell them it's amazing.

490
00:27:51.128 --> 00:27:53.297
-Recommend. not force.
-Yes. Chef!

491
00:27:54.173 --> 00:27:55.424
{\an8}Orders are coming in.

492
00:27:55.508 --> 00:27:58.302
{\an8}Let's make some tasty dishes
the customers will love.

493
00:27:58.386 --> 00:28:01.305
{\an8}Table 1. two specials.
Table 2. two seafood gratins.

494
00:28:01.389 --> 00:28:02.223
Fire!

495
00:28:10.564 --> 00:28:11.649
-Hey. Joon.
-Yes.

496
00:28:11.732 --> 00:28:12.817
-Noodles.
-Yes. sir.

497
00:28:31.669 --> 00:28:34.422
Okay. Table 5. two steak pastas.
one special.

498
00:28:34.505 --> 00:28:37.550
Table 11. 1 special. 1 sun salad.
2 specials. Together.

499
00:28:37.633 --> 00:28:38.717
Yes. Chef!

500
00:28:38.801 --> 00:28:40.052
Table 8. two specials.

501
00:28:40.136 --> 00:28:41.137
Come on.

502
00:28:41.846 --> 00:28:43.973
I'll take the special.
Min-soo. pasta.

503
00:28:44.056 --> 00:28:44.890
Yes. Chef.

504
00:28:44.974 --> 00:28:46.976
-Dong-chul. you take salad.
-Yes. Chef.

505
00:28:47.059 --> 00:28:48.644
-Ji-woong. take orders.
-Yes. Chef.

506
00:28:48.727 --> 00:28:49.895
Bong. bring it now!

507
00:28:49.979 --> 00:28:51.355
Yes. I'm sorry. Chef.

508
00:28:52.064 --> 00:28:53.065
Here it is.

509
00:28:55.609 --> 00:28:57.611
Here. Bong. Fill up the water.

510
00:28:58.237 --> 00:28:59.238
Water.

511
00:29:02.867 --> 00:29:03.951
Cook garlic again.

512
00:29:05.161 --> 00:29:06.328
-Hey. Min-soo.
-Yes.

513
00:29:06.412 --> 00:29:08.747
-Table 5 is beautiful. Be good.
-I saw them.

514
00:29:23.679 --> 00:29:24.597
More salt.

515
00:29:43.491 --> 00:29:46.160
You're so noisy! Stay still!

516
00:29:46.243 --> 00:29:48.537
I can't.
Why did you put a bell on me?

517
00:29:52.500 --> 00:29:55.085
It hurts!

518
00:29:56.962 --> 00:29:58.088
Good job. Finish up.

519
00:29:58.172 --> 00:30:00.382
-Yes. Chef. thank you.
-Good job. Chef.

520
00:30:00.466 --> 00:30:01.467
Well. Chef.

521
00:30:01.550 --> 00:30:04.512
If you don't have a plan.
shall we have a drink?

522
00:30:04.595 --> 00:30:06.305
Don't say things you don't mean.

523
00:30:06.388 --> 00:30:07.264
I'll go work out.

524
00:30:07.348 --> 00:30:09.350
-Bye. guys.
-Yes. Chef.

525
00:30:09.433 --> 00:30:11.769
-Good work.
-Good work.

526
00:30:11.852 --> 00:30:12.770
Good night.

527
00:30:12.853 --> 00:30:15.439
He sure can read the room.

528
00:30:15.523 --> 00:30:18.108
-Let's wash up and go.
-Okay.

529
00:30:22.488 --> 00:30:23.489
-Bye.
-Bye.

530
00:30:25.616 --> 00:30:26.534
Bye.

531
00:30:33.791 --> 00:30:38.003
I cooked at least
100 dishes of noodles today.

532
00:30:38.087 --> 00:30:40.297
Why so many customers?
It's annoying.

533
00:30:40.381 --> 00:30:41.674
Still.

534
00:30:41.757 --> 00:30:45.052
he might raise our pay
if business does well. don't you think?

535
00:30:45.135 --> 00:30:46.845
I doubt it.

536
00:30:46.929 --> 00:30:48.013
Hey. look at him.

537
00:30:48.097 --> 00:30:50.432
He doesn't treat us
as well as his sister.

538
00:30:50.516 --> 00:30:52.935
Eun-hee is not an ordinary sister.

539
00:30:53.018 --> 00:30:54.270
She's different.

540
00:30:54.353 --> 00:30:57.273
She once was an elegant ballet dancer

541
00:30:57.356 --> 00:30:59.650
and can't use her legs
after a hit-and-run.

542
00:30:59.733 --> 00:31:01.652
He must feel so bad for his sister.

543
00:31:01.735 --> 00:31:04.488
That's why they say
the heavens are impartial.

544
00:31:04.572 --> 00:31:05.781
Instead.

545
00:31:05.864 --> 00:31:08.659
she has a successful brother
and a reliable husband.

546
00:31:09.535 --> 00:31:10.953
How nice is that?

547
00:31:11.036 --> 00:31:12.288
Reliable and successful...

548
00:31:15.958 --> 00:31:17.334
<i>Cordon</i>. you punk.

549
00:31:17.418 --> 00:31:19.378
You're staring at me.

550
00:31:19.461 --> 00:31:20.462
At <i>Cordon</i>. do they...

551
00:31:20.546 --> 00:31:22.339
-They don't.
-They didn't?

552
00:31:22.423 --> 00:31:24.675
Come on. Sous Chef. Let's go.

553
00:31:24.758 --> 00:31:26.969
Sous Chef. it's time for your medicine.

554
00:31:27.052 --> 00:31:28.095
What medicine today?

555
00:31:28.178 --> 00:31:29.847
-Soju or beer?
-Mixed.

556
00:31:30.598 --> 00:31:32.391
-Mix them up?
-Shall we?

557
00:31:33.225 --> 00:31:36.061
Darn it! I can't do this.

558
00:31:36.145 --> 00:31:38.981
He's so much younger than me!

559
00:31:39.064 --> 00:31:40.733
He thinks Sous Chef is so amazing?

560
00:31:40.816 --> 00:31:42.484
He's the king. huh?

561
00:31:42.568 --> 00:31:44.778
I just want to tell him the truth

562
00:31:44.862 --> 00:31:46.405
and punch him in the face!

563
00:31:46.488 --> 00:31:47.531
Shut up. you punk!

564
00:31:48.741 --> 00:31:49.825
Damn it.

565
00:31:49.908 --> 00:31:52.077
Why did you lie about your age?

566
00:31:52.161 --> 00:31:54.246
I had no option I always got rejected

567
00:31:54.330 --> 00:31:56.081
even without an interview for my age.

568
00:31:56.749 --> 00:31:58.417
I should've just kept fixing cars.

569
00:31:58.500 --> 00:32:00.294
Maybe I shouldn't have started cooking.

570
00:32:00.377 --> 00:32:02.338
Dong-chul. aren't you coming?

571
00:32:02.421 --> 00:32:05.049
Gosh. I'm on my way.

572
00:32:05.132 --> 00:32:06.216
You're so impatient.

573
00:32:11.805 --> 00:32:13.641
I'm all dressed. Come in.

574
00:33:08.654 --> 00:33:10.155
Yes. enjoy.

575
00:33:33.554 --> 00:33:35.305
JUNGANG GOSIWON

576
00:33:43.147 --> 00:33:45.441
Oh. so loud.

577
00:33:45.524 --> 00:33:46.900
It's too loud.

578
00:33:46.984 --> 00:33:49.445
I can't concentrate because of that.

579
00:33:49.528 --> 00:33:51.697
I'm sorry.

580
00:33:51.780 --> 00:33:55.993
I'm a kitchen assistant and
have to practice.

581
00:33:56.076 --> 00:33:57.077
I'll be careful.

582
00:33:57.619 --> 00:33:59.496
Everyone is a chef these days.

583
00:33:59.580 --> 00:34:01.415
TV ruined everything.

584
00:34:03.208 --> 00:34:04.209
I'm sorry.

585
00:34:13.761 --> 00:34:17.473
<i>I was frail and had stomachache
all the time as a child.</i>

586
00:34:17.556 --> 00:34:20.976
<i>My grandmother used to make
this cabbage porridge for me.</i>

587
00:34:21.560 --> 00:34:24.730
<i>She warned she'd have my finger pricked
if I refuse to eat.</i>

588
00:34:24.813 --> 00:34:27.733
<i>I forced myself to eat cabbage porridge.</i>

589
00:34:28.525 --> 00:34:31.153
<i>Remembering my grandma's love
that soothed my stomach</i>

590
00:34:31.236 --> 00:34:33.739
<i>and comforted my heart.</i>

591
00:34:33.822 --> 00:34:37.326
<i>I'm posting the cabbage porridge recipe
today.</i>

592
00:34:38.869 --> 00:34:40.954
Unit 305. you have a package.

593
00:34:41.038 --> 00:34:42.372
Oh. okay.

594
00:35:20.577 --> 00:35:22.579
Excuse me.

595
00:35:22.663 --> 00:35:23.914
Yes. ma'am.

596
00:35:23.997 --> 00:35:27.042
The soup's cold
and the picture hasn't come up real.

597
00:35:27.543 --> 00:35:28.669
Heat it up again.

598
00:35:29.461 --> 00:35:33.674
Oh. the noodles would get soggy
and it won't taste good...

599
00:35:35.050 --> 00:35:36.260
Hey.

600
00:35:36.343 --> 00:35:38.595
I've been a gourmet blogger
for five years.

601
00:35:38.679 --> 00:35:41.640
I know all of that. Just heat it up.

602
00:35:43.225 --> 00:35:44.393
Yes. ma'am.

603
00:35:49.064 --> 00:35:50.732
Why is it...?

604
00:35:50.816 --> 00:35:53.193
Mom. let's play.

605
00:35:53.277 --> 00:35:55.445
Wait. sweetheart. I'm working. One second.

606
00:35:56.238 --> 00:35:57.865
It's not working.

607
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:08.166
What are you doing?

608
00:36:08.917 --> 00:36:11.003
-Oh. well...
-Hurry up.

609
00:36:18.010 --> 00:36:19.177
Oh my! Hot!

610
00:36:20.220 --> 00:36:22.431
Jun-soo. are you okay?
You didn't get burned?

611
00:36:22.514 --> 00:36:23.640
Oh my goodness!

612
00:36:24.224 --> 00:36:25.559
Are you okay. kid?

613
00:36:26.143 --> 00:36:27.185
What are you doing?

614
00:36:27.269 --> 00:36:29.521
You should be more cautious
with hot stuff.

615
00:36:29.980 --> 00:36:31.773
What if my son got burned?

616
00:36:31.857 --> 00:36:33.609
I'm sorry.

617
00:36:33.692 --> 00:36:36.069
Children are supposed to run around.

618
00:36:36.153 --> 00:36:39.072
Adults should be careful.
Children can't take care of adults.

619
00:36:39.156 --> 00:36:41.199
Employee training is such a joke here!

620
00:36:41.283 --> 00:36:43.535
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

621
00:36:43.619 --> 00:36:46.163
How old are you?
You go to kindergarten?

622
00:36:46.705 --> 00:36:49.124
You learned you shouldn't run
in public places?

623
00:36:49.207 --> 00:36:50.918
-I did.
-You did?

624
00:36:51.001 --> 00:36:52.336
Then did you do wrong or not?

625
00:36:52.419 --> 00:36:54.421
-I did wrong.
-Right? You did wrong.

626
00:36:54.504 --> 00:36:55.714
What are you doing?

627
00:36:55.797 --> 00:36:56.798
Why?

628
00:36:57.799 --> 00:36:59.760
Are you mad
because your kid got scolded?

629
00:36:59.843 --> 00:37:03.513
I'm mad because
you were scolding my employee.

630
00:37:03.597 --> 00:37:05.140
I cannot believe this.

631
00:37:05.223 --> 00:37:07.351
Exactly. I can't believe this.

632
00:37:07.434 --> 00:37:10.020
Whether it gets soggy or not.
you said heat it up.

633
00:37:10.103 --> 00:37:12.230
If the dish doesn't taste good.
then you'd...

634
00:37:13.023 --> 00:37:15.525
Let go. That alone is nonsensical.

635
00:37:15.609 --> 00:37:16.860
Your kid is out of control.

636
00:37:16.944 --> 00:37:18.779
yet you blame someone else?

637
00:37:18.862 --> 00:37:20.280
What. are you done talking?

638
00:37:20.364 --> 00:37:21.698
So you were on TV?

639
00:37:21.782 --> 00:37:23.784
Ma'am. please calm down.

640
00:37:23.867 --> 00:37:24.952
Who are you?

641
00:37:27.162 --> 00:37:28.413
Nothing is normal here.

642
00:37:39.383 --> 00:37:40.884
{\an8}-Get out.
-Let go!

643
00:37:40.968 --> 00:37:42.427
{\an8}-Get out!
-This is crazy.

644
00:37:42.511 --> 00:37:44.262
{\an8}Oh my! Jun-soo.

645
00:37:44.346 --> 00:37:46.056
{\an8}Crazy people aren't welcome here.

646
00:37:46.139 --> 00:37:47.683
{\an8}Just go.

647
00:37:47.766 --> 00:37:48.976
This is ridiculous.

648
00:37:49.059 --> 00:37:50.435
Let's go. Jun-soo!

649
00:37:50.519 --> 00:37:52.229
I won't let it slide!

650
00:37:52.312 --> 00:37:54.773
Excuse me. you dropped your credit card...

651
00:37:54.856 --> 00:37:56.358
I'll make you regret. Let's go!

652
00:37:56.441 --> 00:37:57.275
I'm sorry.

653
00:37:58.235 --> 00:37:59.653
Good-bye.

654
00:38:02.072 --> 00:38:02.990
Hey.

655
00:38:04.574 --> 00:38:07.661
-I'm sorry.
-Oh. come on!

656
00:38:15.293 --> 00:38:16.294
Come in.

657
00:38:19.548 --> 00:38:20.549
Oh. my God.

658
00:38:24.261 --> 00:38:25.929
I'm sorry. Chef.

659
00:38:26.013 --> 00:38:27.806
I should have been more careful.

660
00:38:27.889 --> 00:38:29.307
You know why I don't like you?

661
00:38:29.891 --> 00:38:31.810
-Sorry?
-Your attitude annoys me.

662
00:38:32.477 --> 00:38:35.313
Whether you're at fault or not.
you always say sorry

663
00:38:35.397 --> 00:38:37.482
and blame yourself.
That's your attitude.

664
00:38:38.692 --> 00:38:41.862
That's not being nice.

665
00:38:41.945 --> 00:38:43.405
You always say. "It's my fault."

666
00:38:43.488 --> 00:38:45.532
It gives people around you a hard time.

667
00:38:46.241 --> 00:38:47.993
I'm sorry...

668
00:38:51.288 --> 00:38:54.124
Kitchen's not an easy place.
It's a battlefield.

669
00:38:54.916 --> 00:38:56.877
Only the strong survive.

670
00:38:56.960 --> 00:39:00.088
If you see yourself as weak.
you won't stand a chance here.

671
00:39:05.802 --> 00:39:07.554
Let me lend you some honest advice.

672
00:39:09.139 --> 00:39:10.557
Think about it carefully

673
00:39:11.308 --> 00:39:13.101
if you really belong to the kitchen.

674
00:39:14.811 --> 00:39:15.937
Don't hold onto it.

675
00:39:16.021 --> 00:39:19.149
only to end up getting hurt
and causing inconvenience to others.

676
00:39:23.695 --> 00:39:26.656
Put on some salve.
You don't want a scar on your hand.

677
00:39:43.298 --> 00:39:44.966
Did you scold Bong-sun a lot?

678
00:39:46.843 --> 00:39:49.262
This was not her fault.

679
00:39:49.346 --> 00:39:50.555
It's not a sin to be nice.

680
00:39:50.639 --> 00:39:52.057
Being too nice is a sin.

681
00:39:55.477 --> 00:39:57.312
But are you going to be okay?

682
00:39:57.395 --> 00:39:59.189
That woman is a power blogger.

683
00:39:59.272 --> 00:40:00.440
Is that a big shot job?

684
00:40:02.150 --> 00:40:03.276
So annoying.

685
00:40:03.360 --> 00:40:06.113
Bloggers are more annoying
than reporters.

686
00:40:06.196 --> 00:40:07.781
Who are they to give points?

687
00:40:07.864 --> 00:40:08.698
On what basis?

688
00:40:10.951 --> 00:40:12.619
They're trying to boss around.

689
00:40:17.207 --> 00:40:19.292
Daemyeong Middle School
Alumni Reunion

690
00:40:22.462 --> 00:40:23.296
Why? What is it?

691
00:40:25.173 --> 00:40:26.091
Just a spam message.

692
00:40:28.927 --> 00:40:30.303
DELETE

693
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:38.436
It got knocked over.

694
00:40:39.062 --> 00:40:40.230
So dirty.

695
00:40:40.897 --> 00:40:42.566
I'm sorry. I'll clean it up.

696
00:40:43.567 --> 00:40:46.194
Hey. it's because of you.

697
00:40:46.278 --> 00:40:48.196
Shut up. bastard.

698
00:40:48.280 --> 00:40:50.407
It's because of this loser. Kang Sun-woo.

699
00:40:51.867 --> 00:40:53.702
Please move your feet...

700
00:40:55.453 --> 00:40:56.371
You clean it up.

701
00:41:09.885 --> 00:41:12.846
<i>Sun-woo. I'm going to be late today.</i>

702
00:41:12.929 --> 00:41:14.764
<i>I'm sorry. I know it's your birthday.</i>

703
00:41:14.848 --> 00:41:16.725
<i>Order some gimbap with this money.</i>

704
00:42:28.463 --> 00:42:31.258
GYEONGGI DINER

705
00:42:31.341 --> 00:42:33.969
-Sir. we're ready to pay.
-Okay.

706
00:42:34.052 --> 00:42:35.428
It's 15.000 won.

707
00:42:35.512 --> 00:42:36.805
-All right.
-Yes.

708
00:42:37.514 --> 00:42:39.224
I'll be there in 10 to 20 minutes.

709
00:42:39.307 --> 00:42:41.017
Okay.

710
00:42:43.228 --> 00:42:44.896
Side dishes were a letdown. huh?

711
00:42:45.272 --> 00:42:46.523
Sorry. I was busy.

712
00:42:47.107 --> 00:42:48.441
No. sir. It was delicious.

713
00:42:49.734 --> 00:42:50.777
Here you go.

714
00:42:51.861 --> 00:42:53.863
You gave me too much change.

715
00:42:54.489 --> 00:42:57.117
Oh. my. What was I thinking?

716
00:42:57.200 --> 00:42:59.536
-I'm sorry.
-You nearly lost all you earned today.

717
00:42:59.619 --> 00:43:01.246
Gosh. exactly.

718
00:43:02.122 --> 00:43:04.207
-Where's Kyung-mo?
-He's meeting his friends.

719
00:43:05.000 --> 00:43:07.502
For me. it's better when he's not around.

720
00:43:08.878 --> 00:43:10.046
Coffee isn't coming out.

721
00:43:10.130 --> 00:43:12.215
What? Again?

722
00:43:12.299 --> 00:43:13.925
Gosh. this thing...

723
00:43:14.009 --> 00:43:15.510
Is it faulty wiring?

724
00:43:16.678 --> 00:43:18.471
Wait. let me open it with the key.

725
00:43:18.555 --> 00:43:20.307
No. It's okay. It's all right.

726
00:43:20.390 --> 00:43:21.891
-Still...
-No. that's okay.

727
00:43:23.101 --> 00:43:24.602
Eun-hee!

728
00:43:24.686 --> 00:43:25.729
Gosh.

729
00:43:25.812 --> 00:43:27.105
Every time you come down.

730
00:43:27.188 --> 00:43:28.481
-it scares me.
-It's okay.

731
00:43:30.525 --> 00:43:31.443
He's here.

732
00:43:36.823 --> 00:43:38.491
-You waited long?
-Not at all.

733
00:43:38.575 --> 00:43:39.909
I had to resolve a complaint.

734
00:43:39.993 --> 00:43:41.244
It's been so long.

735
00:43:41.328 --> 00:43:42.871
-Oh. hello.
-Ah!

736
00:43:42.954 --> 00:43:44.164
What a surprise!

737
00:43:44.831 --> 00:43:47.542
Who is this goddess?
I was totally surprised.

738
00:43:47.625 --> 00:43:48.585
-Hi there.
-Yes.

739
00:43:48.668 --> 00:43:50.712
Officer Han.
you must've changed your go-to.

740
00:43:50.795 --> 00:43:53.256
You don't come for
spicy seafood noodle soup you love.

741
00:43:53.340 --> 00:43:56.176
If you say that. it really bums me out.

742
00:43:56.718 --> 00:43:58.720
That soup is always my favorite.

743
00:43:59.262 --> 00:44:01.931
But I'd have to stand in line to eat it.

744
00:44:02.015 --> 00:44:03.475
There are so many people here.

745
00:44:04.184 --> 00:44:05.477
Not my style.

746
00:44:05.560 --> 00:44:06.895
Star chef. not my thing.

747
00:44:07.020 --> 00:44:07.854
Come on.

748
00:44:07.937 --> 00:44:10.398
I'll reserve a seat especially for you.

749
00:44:10.482 --> 00:44:11.900
-So do come.
-Really?

750
00:44:11.983 --> 00:44:15.028
Nice. I'm happy I set you two up.

751
00:44:15.111 --> 00:44:16.946
-Be good to her.
-Yes. sir.

752
00:44:18.239 --> 00:44:19.699
Where are you going?

753
00:44:19.783 --> 00:44:22.911
Uh. my close friend is
opening a restaurant today.

754
00:44:22.994 --> 00:44:24.287
It calls for a celebration.

755
00:44:24.371 --> 00:44:25.497
So I'll do some nagging.

756
00:44:26.831 --> 00:44:27.916
-Bye. guys.
-Bye.

757
00:44:27.999 --> 00:44:28.875
Bye.

758
00:44:29.542 --> 00:44:31.127
I should go. too.
See you tomorrow.

759
00:44:31.211 --> 00:44:32.545
Good night. Eun-hee.

760
00:44:32.629 --> 00:44:34.130
-Good work. sir.
-Good job.

761
00:44:36.299 --> 00:44:37.967
Shall we go. too?

762
00:44:38.843 --> 00:44:39.761
Yes. honey.

763
00:44:42.263 --> 00:44:44.682
It was a long day.

764
00:44:44.766 --> 00:44:45.600
How about you?

765
00:44:45.683 --> 00:44:47.602
I was busy too.

766
00:44:47.685 --> 00:44:48.937
Hold tight.

767
00:44:49.687 --> 00:44:50.522
There.

768
00:44:53.775 --> 00:44:55.402
Luxurious.

769
00:44:55.485 --> 00:44:58.029
Luxurious. very high-end.

770
00:44:58.113 --> 00:45:00.448
It's so luxurious and
it's the same as mine.

771
00:45:00.532 --> 00:45:01.449
Right.

772
00:45:02.117 --> 00:45:03.743
Did you copy the whole thing?

773
00:45:04.327 --> 00:45:05.245
Yes.

774
00:45:05.829 --> 00:45:08.164
You taught me to copy everything
that's good.

775
00:45:08.248 --> 00:45:09.666
This is just identical.

776
00:45:10.625 --> 00:45:11.793
Now. try it.

777
00:45:11.876 --> 00:45:14.671
You're doing the chef thing again.
All the time.

778
00:45:14.754 --> 00:45:16.214
A chef tastes

779
00:45:16.297 --> 00:45:18.633
50% with his nose
and 50% with his mouth.

780
00:45:18.716 --> 00:45:19.551
That's right.

781
00:45:20.468 --> 00:45:24.722
Finally. Chef Kang Sun-woo
will have a taste.

782
00:45:27.725 --> 00:45:29.352
Drum roll...

783
00:45:37.986 --> 00:45:38.820
It won't fail.

784
00:45:40.655 --> 00:45:43.741
The noodles are nice.
seasoning is spot-on.

785
00:45:43.825 --> 00:45:44.826
Yes.

786
00:45:46.244 --> 00:45:47.662
What's gotten into you?

787
00:45:47.745 --> 00:45:50.415
So can I measure up to your heels?

788
00:45:50.498 --> 00:45:53.001
How can you compare a human with a god?

789
00:45:53.084 --> 00:45:54.502
My cooking is heavenly.

790
00:45:54.586 --> 00:45:55.837
-Here we go.
-Yes!

791
00:45:55.920 --> 00:45:58.047
This is the thing!

792
00:45:58.131 --> 00:46:01.217
Hey. not anyone can hear my advice.
So listen carefully.

793
00:46:01.926 --> 00:46:04.179
Never play with food.

794
00:46:04.262 --> 00:46:06.264
What you put on the plate isn't food.

795
00:46:06.347 --> 00:46:07.223
It's your faces.

796
00:46:10.977 --> 00:46:13.271
Don't stop me. I'll cause some trouble.

797
00:46:13.354 --> 00:46:14.814
-Big time.
-What?

798
00:46:14.898 --> 00:46:17.108
Wang-joo is here.

799
00:46:17.192 --> 00:46:18.943
You can't see her easily.

800
00:46:19.027 --> 00:46:20.737
Have a seat.

801
00:46:20.820 --> 00:46:23.531
Wang-joo. Let me introduce yourself.

802
00:46:23.615 --> 00:46:26.117
This is Wang-joo. She is just amazing.

803
00:46:26.201 --> 00:46:28.286
You know him. right? Chef Kang Sun-woo.

804
00:46:28.369 --> 00:46:29.370
-Hello.
-Hello.

805
00:46:29.454 --> 00:46:31.122
Chef Choi Sung-woo over there.

806
00:47:01.569 --> 00:47:04.197
Right. you lit it again.

807
00:47:04.280 --> 00:47:05.323
I knew it.

808
00:47:07.575 --> 00:47:08.660
I'm sorry.

809
00:47:08.743 --> 00:47:10.537
Saying sorry won't help. lady.

810
00:47:10.620 --> 00:47:12.205
I told you so many times.

811
00:47:12.914 --> 00:47:14.332
This room has no window.

812
00:47:14.415 --> 00:47:16.334
It could catch on fire.

813
00:47:16.417 --> 00:47:17.919
It's not ventilated.

814
00:47:18.670 --> 00:47:20.255
People are fed up with it.

815
00:47:20.338 --> 00:47:21.631
I'm sorry.

816
00:47:21.714 --> 00:47:23.591
-I'll be careful. sir.
-Oh. forget it.

817
00:47:24.175 --> 00:47:26.094
I can't stand it.
Find another place.

818
00:47:26.177 --> 00:47:27.595
But sir...

819
00:47:28.388 --> 00:47:30.473
Not just this incense.

820
00:47:31.474 --> 00:47:33.643
but these weird things on the wall.

821
00:47:34.227 --> 00:47:36.020
I can't stand it anymore.

822
00:47:36.104 --> 00:47:37.647
Leave as soon as possible. okay?

823
00:47:38.523 --> 00:47:39.524
But sir...

824
00:47:58.668 --> 00:48:00.670
BONG-SUN'S SCRAPBOOK

825
00:48:16.477 --> 00:48:21.524
"Cooking is like music."
Kang Sun-woo -Chef/owner of Sun Restaurant

826
00:48:21.608 --> 00:48:23.359
<i>You always say. "It's my fault."</i>

827
00:48:23.443 --> 00:48:25.528
<i>It gives people around you a hard time.</i>

828
00:48:26.321 --> 00:48:27.780
<i>Think about it carefully</i>

829
00:48:28.406 --> 00:48:30.199
<i>if you really belong to the kitchen.</i>

830
00:48:32.035 --> 00:48:33.328
<i>Don't hold onto it.</i>

831
00:48:33.411 --> 00:48:36.706
<i>only to end up getting hurt
and causing inconvenience to others.</i>

832
00:48:37.373 --> 00:48:39.709
Chef Kang Sun-woo

833
00:48:42.879 --> 00:48:45.006
"When I see the faces
of people enjoying..."

834
00:49:26.673 --> 00:49:28.841
-I'm sorry.
-Look where you're going.

835
00:49:53.574 --> 00:49:55.993
It's actually my birthday next week.

836
00:49:56.577 --> 00:49:58.413
so I'm planning a party.

837
00:49:58.496 --> 00:50:00.498
Can you cook food for us?

838
00:50:01.124 --> 00:50:03.084
All my friends are your fans.

839
00:50:04.669 --> 00:50:07.130
What do I do?
It'll be expensive to hire me.

840
00:50:09.340 --> 00:50:11.134
I'm kidding. I can't even joke around?

841
00:50:11.217 --> 00:50:13.094
You don't even let me say anything.

842
00:50:13.177 --> 00:50:15.388
Well. you're not gonna ask for a building.

843
00:50:16.055 --> 00:50:17.473
I'll pay whatever you ask for.

844
00:50:17.557 --> 00:50:19.225
You can ask a lot.

845
00:50:19.308 --> 00:50:22.270
She's a daughter of Yeongchang Group CEO.

846
00:50:22.353 --> 00:50:23.396
Oh. really?

847
00:50:24.355 --> 00:50:26.899
I was going to do it since you're pretty.
but too bad.

848
00:50:26.983 --> 00:50:28.568
I think I'll have a plan that day.

849
00:50:28.943 --> 00:50:30.361
I'm sorry.

850
00:50:31.946 --> 00:50:33.614
I forgot I had a plan. I'll go.

851
00:50:34.782 --> 00:50:36.117
Why?

852
00:50:36.200 --> 00:50:37.201
Stay longer.

853
00:50:40.329 --> 00:50:41.289
What's the matter?

854
00:50:41.914 --> 00:50:43.332
Have some coffee and stay.

855
00:50:44.584 --> 00:50:46.169
I'm meeting someone over coffee.

856
00:50:46.252 --> 00:50:47.587
-Really? A woman?
-Yes.

857
00:50:47.670 --> 00:50:50.214
Wouldn't it be strange
if I meet a man at this hour?

858
00:50:52.800 --> 00:50:54.302
-Here. take it.
-Seriously.

859
00:50:54.385 --> 00:50:56.220
I didn't even get a plant for you.

860
00:50:56.304 --> 00:50:57.138
Take it.

861
00:50:57.722 --> 00:50:58.639
Well...

862
00:50:59.348 --> 00:51:00.391
I'll do my best.

863
00:51:01.100 --> 00:51:02.143
By the way. Jung-woo.

864
00:51:03.102 --> 00:51:04.520
Don't get too close with

865
00:51:04.604 --> 00:51:07.523
Yeongchang Group's daughter
or whatever in there. Okay?

866
00:51:09.901 --> 00:51:12.904
Work hard. punk.
I heard it was all financed through loans.

867
00:51:12.987 --> 00:51:13.905
Bye.

868
00:51:24.499 --> 00:51:25.333
I love you. bro.

869
00:51:26.042 --> 00:51:29.045
For a handsome guy.
The golden ratio. Here.

870
00:51:29.128 --> 00:51:30.588
Thank you.

871
00:51:36.052 --> 00:51:38.471
Your coffee is the best.

872
00:51:38.554 --> 00:51:39.597
Perfect for hangover.

873
00:51:41.015 --> 00:51:42.683
You came late after a drink today.

874
00:51:42.767 --> 00:51:44.060
No. you're too early.

875
00:51:44.143 --> 00:51:45.645
Well. it doesn't matter.

876
00:51:45.728 --> 00:51:48.856
I'll enjoy coffee and get some good stuff.

877
00:51:49.482 --> 00:51:51.192
-Bye. then.
-Bye. Mr. handsome.

878
00:51:54.278 --> 00:51:55.780
Come see abalones. So fresh.

879
00:51:56.614 --> 00:51:57.782
-Come later.
-Sure.

880
00:52:06.791 --> 00:52:08.209
That cuttlefish.

881
00:52:09.752 --> 00:52:10.795
So fresh and nice.

882
00:52:10.878 --> 00:52:13.089
Mr. Handsome.
Here's a good deal on octopus.

883
00:52:13.172 --> 00:52:14.257
Get this one.

884
00:52:14.340 --> 00:52:16.050
No.

885
00:52:16.133 --> 00:52:17.134
Octopus for later.

886
00:52:17.218 --> 00:52:20.263
-Is squid fresh. ma'am?
-Fresh and nice.

887
00:52:20.346 --> 00:52:21.931
Clams look fresh too.

888
00:52:23.224 --> 00:52:24.392
Let me look around.

889
00:52:24.517 --> 00:52:26.102
Check out mackerels.

890
00:52:26.185 --> 00:52:28.646
-Okay.
-Gosh.

891
00:52:28.729 --> 00:52:30.898
You should buy something
if you're here.

892
00:52:30.982 --> 00:52:32.108
Oh my!

893
00:52:34.861 --> 00:52:36.571
You're not going to buy it again?

894
00:52:36.654 --> 00:52:39.073
It's not fresh. How can I?

895
00:52:39.156 --> 00:52:41.117
Don't sell stuff like this.

896
00:52:41.200 --> 00:52:42.493
You'll have a bad image.

897
00:52:42.577 --> 00:52:44.495
You have such a good eye.

898
00:52:44.579 --> 00:52:46.914
Shrimp. it really came in today.

899
00:52:48.165 --> 00:52:49.333
It's fine.

900
00:52:49.417 --> 00:52:51.961
It's great. There's no need to check.

901
00:52:52.044 --> 00:52:54.463
Nice color. nice shell. Good.

902
00:52:54.547 --> 00:52:55.631
Three kilos of this.

903
00:52:56.591 --> 00:52:58.509
Three kilos that are like five kilos.

904
00:52:59.218 --> 00:53:00.219
You rascal.

905
00:53:41.928 --> 00:53:42.845
What?

906
00:53:44.055 --> 00:53:45.014
Who is it?

907
00:53:46.265 --> 00:53:47.266
Bong-sun?

908
00:53:49.352 --> 00:53:50.436
What are you doing?

909
00:53:53.689 --> 00:53:54.607
Are you coming in?

910
00:53:54.690 --> 00:53:57.485
Coming in... I mean. I'm leaving.

911
00:53:58.069 --> 00:53:59.153
What are you saying?

912
00:53:59.236 --> 00:54:00.780
Well. let me...

913
00:54:00.863 --> 00:54:01.781
Bring it.

914
00:54:31.644 --> 00:54:33.562
{\an8}KANG SUN-WOO

915
00:54:36.023 --> 00:54:36.899
{\an8}What?

916
00:54:37.566 --> 00:54:38.609
My ranking went down.

917
00:54:39.735 --> 00:54:41.153
Seriously.

918
00:54:41.654 --> 00:54:43.239
Why is Marco second place?

919
00:54:46.867 --> 00:54:49.078
{\an8}With Jeong Eun-woo
a star on SBC drama series

920
00:54:49.161 --> 00:54:50.621
{\an8}Gosh.

921
00:54:50.705 --> 00:54:53.332
He blogged pictures of himself
with celebrities.

922
00:54:56.627 --> 00:54:57.795
{\an8}Look at him.

923
00:54:58.796 --> 00:55:01.340
He's got no skills. just connections.

924
00:55:01.424 --> 00:55:02.883
Jeez.

925
00:55:02.967 --> 00:55:03.801
Get lost.

926
00:55:07.138 --> 00:55:10.850
You are my sunshine.

927
00:55:10.933 --> 00:55:13.060
Little joys of everyday life.

928
00:55:13.144 --> 00:55:14.854
Dreaming of happy. warm table.

929
00:55:14.937 --> 00:55:17.023
See? How nice is it?

930
00:55:18.858 --> 00:55:22.445
Cabbage... is a good ingredient.

931
00:55:23.279 --> 00:55:26.449
This person is so genuine in cooking.

932
00:55:28.159 --> 00:55:30.619
I feel sincerity from this blog.

933
00:55:37.334 --> 00:55:39.712
Dear Sunshine. your recipes

934
00:55:42.131 --> 00:55:48.137
always carry happiness that can be tasted.

935
00:55:50.473 --> 00:55:51.390
I'm a fan.

936
00:55:52.308 --> 00:55:53.142
You got this.

937
00:55:54.143 --> 00:55:55.144
No.

938
00:55:55.227 --> 00:55:56.353
You're the bomb.

939
00:56:03.194 --> 00:56:04.361
Maybe a chef?

940
00:56:05.237 --> 00:56:06.906
-Maybe not.
<i>-Chef.</i>

941
00:56:06.989 --> 00:56:09.158
<i>Thank you for everything.</i>

942
00:56:10.076 --> 00:56:12.369
<i>What you said is right.</i>

943
00:56:12.453 --> 00:56:15.873
<i>Doing what I want to do
and being able to do are different.</i>

944
00:56:15.956 --> 00:56:17.625
<i>I was too ambitious.</i>

945
00:56:18.334 --> 00:56:20.961
<i>I'm sorry to the staff as well.</i>

946
00:56:21.045 --> 00:56:22.880
<i>Bye. everyone.</i>

947
00:56:24.173 --> 00:56:26.217
<i>And this is something</i>

948
00:56:26.300 --> 00:56:29.011
<i>I couldn't write in the letter.</i>

949
00:56:29.095 --> 00:56:32.389
<i>Chef. I learned another thing from you.</i>

950
00:56:32.473 --> 00:56:34.892
<i>Human emotions are like a cold.</i>

951
00:56:34.975 --> 00:56:36.936
<i>Once you come down with it.</i>

952
00:56:37.019 --> 00:56:38.437
<i>no matter how hard you resist.</i>

953
00:56:38.521 --> 00:56:41.065
<i>you need to go through it
to get past it.</i>

954
00:56:41.148 --> 00:56:43.317
Whether your dream
is to be a chef or not.

955
00:56:43.400 --> 00:56:44.610
let's work together well.

956
00:56:45.277 --> 00:56:47.696
-Help her a lot.
-Yes. Chef.

957
00:56:54.954 --> 00:56:56.664
Who puts garbage on my plate?

958
00:56:59.750 --> 00:57:01.919
You'd hate eating garbage
on your plate. right?

959
00:57:02.711 --> 00:57:03.671
Do it again.

960
00:57:07.174 --> 00:57:10.052
<i>I wanted to become a chef like you.</i>

961
00:57:14.098 --> 00:57:16.392
Hey. like this. Watch.

962
00:57:17.184 --> 00:57:18.978
Hold it like you grab an egg.

963
00:57:19.061 --> 00:57:21.689
Cut it straight like this.

964
00:57:21.772 --> 00:57:23.357
Do it again.

965
00:57:23.440 --> 00:57:28.195
<i>Because of you. I was excited.
Because of you. I was happy.</i>

966
00:57:28.279 --> 00:57:30.573
<i>Because of you. I was hurt</i>

967
00:57:30.656 --> 00:57:34.076
<i>and hurt again and again.</i>

968
00:57:35.536 --> 00:57:37.663
<i>I've gone through it enough.
so I'm leaving.</i>

969
00:57:38.747 --> 00:57:43.043
<i>For someone like me who's not ordinary.
Sun Restaurant was like a nest.</i>

970
00:57:43.127 --> 00:57:46.297
<i>The world will probably
push me away again.</i>

971
00:57:46.380 --> 00:57:48.048
<i>Still. I'm leaving.</i>

972
00:57:49.049 --> 00:57:51.343
<i>Goodbye. Chef.</i>

973
00:58:33.469 --> 00:58:34.553
What?

974
00:58:34.637 --> 00:58:36.096
<i>Chef. it's me.</i>

975
00:58:36.180 --> 00:58:38.098
<i>I think Bong-sun quit.</i>

976
00:58:40.059 --> 00:58:41.185
Who?

977
00:58:42.353 --> 00:58:46.273
Leaving without saying goodbye...
Bong-sun is so cold.

978
00:58:47.483 --> 00:58:49.902
I'm sure she had no courage
to tell us in person.

979
00:58:51.070 --> 00:58:53.489
Wire her three months' worth of wages
for this month.

980
00:58:53.572 --> 00:58:54.782
Okay.

981
00:58:54.865 --> 00:58:55.908
Chef.

982
00:58:55.991 --> 00:58:57.785
Chef.

983
00:58:57.868 --> 00:59:00.788
The key to the back storage is missing.

984
00:59:00.871 --> 00:59:03.415
I think Bong-sun took it.

985
00:59:04.166 --> 00:59:06.210
-What do you mean? Bong-sun?
-Yes.

986
00:59:08.879 --> 00:59:10.839
-Well. let me...
-Bring it.

987
00:59:13.592 --> 00:59:15.386
SUN - SHRIMP. 3kg

988
00:59:16.804 --> 00:59:19.306
You looked everywhere?
Are you sure it's Bong-sun?

989
00:59:19.390 --> 00:59:21.225
It's gone.
I checked everywhere.

990
00:59:21.850 --> 00:59:22.851
What do we do?

991
00:59:22.935 --> 00:59:25.271
It's gonna take some time
to make that special key.

992
00:59:25.688 --> 00:59:27.147
It's 10:00 a.m. already.

993
00:59:27.231 --> 00:59:29.024
Call her. She must be close by.

994
00:59:29.108 --> 00:59:30.401
She's not picking up either.

995
00:59:30.484 --> 00:59:32.236
Seriously.

996
00:59:32.319 --> 00:59:33.737
Until the end...

997
00:59:34.363 --> 00:59:36.073
-Keep calling her.
-Yes. Chef.

998
00:59:36.615 --> 00:59:39.201
Joon. go to the locksmith
and look into it.

999
00:59:39.285 --> 00:59:41.370
Dong-chul and Min-soo.
start on the dough.

1000
00:59:41.453 --> 00:59:42.579
-Yes. Chef.
-Yes. Chef.

1001
00:59:51.255 --> 00:59:54.967
<i>A room with a window is 350.000 won.
plus 50.000 won maintenance a month.</i>

1002
00:59:55.050 --> 00:59:56.302
<i>It's not available often.</i>

1003
00:59:56.760 --> 00:59:59.013
A room with ventilation is expensive.

1004
01:00:03.142 --> 01:00:05.019
JI-WOONG

1005
01:00:06.770 --> 01:00:08.230
I'm sorry. Ji-woong.

1006
01:00:16.947 --> 01:00:17.990
Headache.

1007
01:00:18.824 --> 01:00:20.326
What's wrong with me?

1008
01:00:20.868 --> 01:00:24.079
I'm so bored.

1009
01:00:24.163 --> 01:00:26.790
I'm so bored that I'm going crazy.

1010
01:00:26.874 --> 01:00:28.292
-Hi
-Jeez.

1011
01:00:28.375 --> 01:00:29.877
You're so noisy.

1012
01:00:29.960 --> 01:00:31.795
I can't poop in peace because of you.

1013
01:00:31.920 --> 01:00:34.173
I'm just so bored.

1014
01:00:34.256 --> 01:00:36.800
There's no customers
at a fortune teller's house.

1015
01:00:36.884 --> 01:00:38.635
It's all because of you.

1016
01:00:38.719 --> 01:00:41.764
You're completely ruining my business.

1017
01:00:41.847 --> 01:00:44.224
So let me go.

1018
01:00:44.308 --> 01:00:46.268
Nothing good will come out of this.

1019
01:00:46.352 --> 01:00:50.564
If you let me go.
I'll live quietly like I'm dead.

1020
01:00:50.647 --> 01:00:52.816
Live like you're dead?
You're already dead.

1021
01:00:52.900 --> 01:00:55.319
-If you were me. would you believe that?
-No.

1022
01:00:56.945 --> 01:00:59.031
Is it a customer?
It must be a customer.

1023
01:00:59.114 --> 01:01:00.449
It's bossam.

1024
01:01:00.532 --> 01:01:02.076
Bossam? Sounds good.

1025
01:01:02.785 --> 01:01:03.994
Noodles are good too.

1026
01:01:06.955 --> 01:01:08.624
-Hello.
-Bossam.

1027
01:01:08.707 --> 01:01:09.917
It's 35.000 won.

1028
01:01:10.584 --> 01:01:11.919
-35.000 won? Here.
-Yes. Huh?

1029
01:01:12.503 --> 01:01:14.088
You should've told us beforehand.

1030
01:01:14.963 --> 01:01:16.548
Why should I?

1031
01:01:16.632 --> 01:01:17.716
If you'd known.

1032
01:01:17.800 --> 01:01:19.218
you would've taken some out?

1033
01:01:19.301 --> 01:01:22.012
That's not it.
Boss is gonna kill me.

1034
01:01:22.096 --> 01:01:23.764
No. Come on.

1035
01:01:23.847 --> 01:01:25.766
I'll call the owner.

1036
01:01:26.225 --> 01:01:27.267
Seriously...

1037
01:01:27.351 --> 01:01:29.770
Hey. don't even think about running away.

1038
01:01:32.481 --> 01:01:33.482
Wait. this wench...

1039
01:01:34.400 --> 01:01:36.819
Just my luck!

1040
01:01:37.569 --> 01:01:39.238
-Out of my way!
-Ma'am.

1041
01:01:40.406 --> 01:01:42.408
-Ma'am!
-I'm going nuts.

1042
01:01:54.253 --> 01:01:55.254
Stop there!

1043
01:01:56.505 --> 01:01:57.589
Damn it.

1044
01:01:58.382 --> 01:01:59.425
Stop right there!

1045
01:01:59.508 --> 01:02:01.176
Let's settle this once and for all.

1046
01:02:03.929 --> 01:02:04.930
That little...

1047
01:02:06.140 --> 01:02:08.142
Stop right there. you wench!

1048
01:02:56.690 --> 01:02:58.484
Where the hell is she hiding?

1049
01:03:01.862 --> 01:03:02.863
